fields.value: Effects of cross-modal asynchrony on informational masking in human cortex

dsDescriptionValue.value: Sounds from "Hausfeld, L., Gutschalk, A., Formisano, E., Riecke, L. (2017).  Effects of cross-modal asynchrony on informational masking in human cortex. Journal of Cognitive Neuroscience". Informational masking paradigm containing a pulsating tone (target) embedded in a multi-tone cloud (masker).

publicationCitation.value: Hausfeld, L., Gutschalk, A., Formisano, E., Riecke, L. (2017).  Effects of cross-modal asynchrony on informational masking in human cortex. Journal of Cognitive Neuroscience

fields.value: The full set of sounds used in our study. Filenames are specified as TF[1-6]_M[1-8]_[0,1]. TF denotes the frequency of the target stream (specifiers 1 to 6 are at 489, 699, 1000, 1430, 2045, or 2924Hz, respectively). M is the masker version with 8 different maskers (random tone positions with jitter in frequency bands; see paper). Final number denotes whether a target was present (1) or not (1). The files ending with target having M0 are targets without masker (pure tone sequences at frequency TF).
